                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1"><P>Join Lonely Planet on a pilgrimage to the roof of the world. Whether your quest is for historical  insight, rugged trekking or quiet revelation, this guide will enlighten you on your journey through Tibet. <ul><li>41 maps for navigating everything from mountains to monasteries </li><li>special sections on the Buddhist pantheon and Lhasa's Jokhang </li><li>hints on cutting through red tape: permits, visas and the Public Security Bureau </li><li>the lowdown on food and drink: learning to love yak-butter tea </li><li>detailed trekking information: how to reach your own Shangri-la </li></ul></span>
              
